description.narrative: All country offices in MENA have strengthened and timely access to high quality technical expertise and programme implementation guidance., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Evaluation And Research, Evaluation And Research (Covid), Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid), Social Protection, Supply And Logistics, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF in the Middle East and North Africa demonstrates strengthened programming excellence for at-scale results for children.

description.narrative: In 2021, the Regional Office (RO) provided on-site and remote demand-driven support to country offices (COs) in line with the regional accelerators road map and 2021 plans. The RO provided support to all COs in all thematic areas while prioritizing humanitarian situations and coronavirus (COVID-19) response. The RO support included facilitation and piloting of headquarters initiatives and systems development roll-outs. Country offices rated ;RO support as highly satisfactory on timeliness and quality dimensions assessed via client satisfaction feedback survey. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/03/2022
